{"TopicId":220164,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Animated stars in skybox.","CreatedByName":"GrapeInvaders","CreatedById":169940,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-23T01:21:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GrapeInvaders","CreatedById":169940,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-23T01:21:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome twinkling of stars in the skybox would make the skies feel so much more alive and less like a spherical image surrounding me. It would be a small detail but not enough games do it and its super immersive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suggested this before but sky dimming on bright surfaces of non-atmospheric moon would also be really cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease? \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-23T01:21:51Z\u0022 title=\u002210/23/2023 01:21  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 23\u0022\u003EOctober 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by GrapeInvaders\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-23T03:20:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStars only twinkle if there\u2019s an atmosphere!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TwoCalories","CreatedById":228871,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-23T03:43:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224332422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698031205\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Periple\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, Periple said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStars only twinkle if there\u2019s an atmosphere!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep. Stars appear to twinkle on the surface of atmospheric bodies like Earth due to the atmosphere \u0022rippling\u0022 or something.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe skybox dimming when looking at the Sun or being in the daylight would be cool, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-23T03:44:23Z\u0022 title=\u002210/23/2023 03:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 23\u0022\u003EOctober 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by TwoCalories\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}